Key Match Events: Donat Rrudhani won a penalty and Vedat Muriqi converted it to give Kosovo a 1-0 lead
Vedat Muriqi scored his second goal in the 21st minute
Albion Rrahmani scored the third goal in the 48th minute
Lumbardh Dellova scored the fourth goal in the 55th minute
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the first win for the Dardanians in the fourth edition of the UEFA Nations League
Others: Coach Franco Foda continued to rotate players, bringing on Ilir Krasniqi, Emir Sahiti, and Eliot Bujupi, who made his debut for the national team
Shortly before the end, Emir Sahiti had a great opportunity to score, but his shot hit the post
